MaurerLines variation:  Added CUBIC_HERMITE_HAPPY_ACCIDENT* render modes. These use incorrect calculations for tangents (based on incorrect derivatives of rose curve). But they yielded some visually interesting curves. Also have some interesting reflection/flipping of x and y components of tangents. Also added XY_SCALE_TANGENT tangent mode to bring reflection/flipping/scaling tangent idea to other render modes. Also commenting out (in preparation for removal) all of the CUBIC_HERMITE_SPLINE[n] experiments. Can now either replicate them in CUBIC_HERMITE_SPLINE mode, or the results were not encouraging enough to keep.

MaurerLines variation: Major revisions to render_modes. WARNING: Any previous test flames will need to be fixed to have render modes remapped to new strategy. Split render_mode param into render_mode, render_submode, and tangent_submode parameters. Many previous separate render_modes are condensed into smaller number of render_modes, while combinatorial variation that gave rise to large numbers of render_modes are refactored into submodes. Eventually most render_modes will support most render_submodes. Tangent_submodes are a a further refactoring of combinatorial variation that was growing within cubic interpolation modes. Also did major refactoring of rendering code, so for example many different render_modes can now share code. Still some refactoring to do on this, but for example it greatly streamlined the growing chunks of code for different cubic Hermite interpolation modes. Also added shape-filling submodes.

MaurerLines variation: got both Kochanek-Bartels splines and cubic Hermite splines using tangent vectors working, as render modes KOCHANEK_BARTELS_SPLINE_FIXED and CUBIC_HERMITE_SPLINE_EXACT_TANGENTS. For KB, there was a bug in my render code. For cubic Hermite, problem was incorrect equations for rhodonea derivatives. Also, moved calculation of derivatives to parametric curve classes. Only one currently implemented is rhodonea, default is to return NaNs. For render modes that need derivatives, if derivatives aren't calculated, defaults to linear interpolation (Maurer lines).
